Learn on the basis of understanding and proficient use of relational databases: 
1. Non-relational database systems, including NoSQL. 
2. Design and model document store and wide column store databases. 
3. Compare and contrast relational and non-relational database modeling. 
4. Explain the concept of transactions in non-relational systems. 
5. Implement document storage and wide column storage systems. 
6. Build applications using graph database systems. 
7. Graphic query processing.
